description: The most elegant, simple, and famous of all Cuban cocktails. The Daiquiri and its variants were set in stone by legendary barman Constantino Ribalaigua of the famous Florida bar in Havana.
source: Smuggler's Cove by Martin Cate with Rebecca Cate
author: Bar La Florida Cocktails, 1935 reprint
